<br>
So it is that the name we choose and the picture we place on message boards comes to define us in the minds of others in way that few perhaps realise when they make their initial and fateful choice.<br>
<br>
On the subject of signatures there has been much discussion.  Does the picture of a dwarf in flagrante-delicto with a rockhopper tell us anything about the author? Perhaps.<br>
<br>
But after years of careful statistical analysis a new and far more effective way of calculating the personality and ultimate worthiness of any individual has been devised.  Are you uncertain whether to allow Auaooioiee into your guild?  Worry no longer, the Aggregate Score System Honorific Accumulated Total will take away the need to get to know the person behind the name and allow you to make a completely arbitrary, but scientifically proven decision about their worth.  Use A.S.S.H.A.T on your friends list and separate the Wheat from the Chaff.<br>
<br>
Simply follow the following instructions (works for forename only)<br>
<br>
1. Count the number of vowels in the name <br>
<br>
2. Deduct the number of consonants<br>
<br>
3. For each double vowel ie &quot;aa&quot;  &quot;ee&quot; -  Add 5<br>
<br>
4. If name is exactly 6 letters long - Minus 1<br>
<br>
5. If name is exactly 5 letters long - Minus 2<br>
<br>
6. If name is exactly 4 letters long - Minus 4<br>
<br>
7. If name is greater than 10 letters long - Add 4<br>
<br>
8. If name is a pun or play on words - Add 5<br>
<br>
9. If name ends with a vowel - Add 2<br>
<br>
10. If name begins with a vowel - Add 2<br>
<br>
11. If name consists entirely of alternating Consonants and Vowels - Minus 4<br>
<br>
12. If name contains name of animal, type of weather, plant, domestic appliance or type of furniture - Add 5<br>
<br>
Results:<br>
<br>
There is no complex sliding scale to the Aggregate Score System Honorific Accumulated Total.<br>
<br>
Put simply a score of less than 0 demonstrates that a person is &quot;our kind of people&quot; and welcome to stay on the server.<br>
<br>
A score of 0 or more denotes a person of dubious character who will probably steal your horse as you are advising newbies on the finer points of roleplay.<br>
<br>
It is suggested that as an addendum to all posts on the board people post their A.S.S.H.A.T. score in brackets, in order to save time and help others decide whether their posts are worth reading or not.<br>
<br>
Thanks<br>
<br>
